  23. ‌let rec struct_const ppf = function
  24.   | Const_base(Const_int n) -> fprintf ppf "%i" n
  25.   | Const_base(Const_char c) -> fprintf ppf "%C" c
  26.   | Const_base(Const_string (s, _, _)) -> fprintf ppf "%S" s
  27.   | Const_immstring s -> fprintf ppf "#%S" s
  28.   | Const_base(Const_float f) -> fprintf ppf "%s" f
  29.   | Const_base(Const_int32 n) -> fprintf ppf "%lil" n
  30.   | Const_base(Const_int64 n) -> fprintf ppf "%LiL" n
  31.   | Const_base(Const_nativeint n) -> fprintf ppf "%nin" n
  32.   | Const_block(tag, []) ->
  33.       fprintf ppf "[%i]" tag
  34.   | Const_block(tag, sc1::scl) ->
  35.       let sconsts ppf scl =
  36.         List.iter (fun sc -> fprintf ppf "@ %a" struct_const sc) scl in
  37.       fprintf ppf "@[<1>[%i:@ @[%a%a@]]@]" tag struct_const sc1 sconsts scl
  38.   | Const_float_array [] ->
  39.       fprintf ppf "[| |]"
  40.   | Const_float_array (f1 :: fl) ->
  41.       let floats ppf fl =
  42.         List.iter (fun f -> fprintf ppf "@ %s" f) fl in
  43.       fprintf ppf "@[<1>[|@[%s%a@]|]@]" f1 floats fl

  107. let record_rep ppf r =
  108.   match r with
  109.   | Record_regular -> fprintf ppf "regular"
  110.   | Record_inlined i -> fprintf ppf "inlined(%i)" i
  111.   | Record_unboxed false -> fprintf ppf "unboxed"
  112.   | Record_unboxed true -> fprintf ppf "inlined(unboxed)"
  113.   | Record_float -> fprintf ppf "float"
  114.   | Record_extension path -> fprintf ppf "ext(%a)" Printtyp.path path

  116. ‌let block_shape ppf shape = match shape with
  117.   | None | Some [] -> ()
  118.   | Some l when List.for_all ((=) Pgenval) l -> ()
  119.   | Some [elt] ->
  120.       Format.fprintf ppf " (%s)" (field_kind elt)
  121.   | Some (h :: t) ->
  122.       Format.fprintf ppf " (%s" (field_kind h);
  123.       List.iter (fun elt ->
  124.           Format.fprintf ppf ",%s" (field_kind elt))
  125.         t;
  126.       Format.fprintf ppf ")"

  136. ‌let float_comparison ppf = function
  137.   | CFeq -> fprintf ppf "==."

  145.   | CFge -> fprintf ppf ">=."
  146.   | CFnge -> fprintf ppf "!>=."

  477. ‌let function_attribute ppf t =
  478.   if t.is_a_functor then
  479.     fprintf ppf "is_a_functor@ ";
  480.   if t.stub then
  481.     fprintf ppf "stub@ ";
  482.   begin match t.inline with
  483.   | Default_inline -> ()
  484.   | Always_inline -> fprintf ppf "always_inline@ "
  485.   | Hint_inline -> fprintf ppf "hint_inline@ "
  486.   | Never_inline -> fprintf ppf "never_inline@ "
  487.   | Unroll i -> fprintf ppf "unroll(%i)@ " i
  488.   end;
  489.   begin match t.specialise with
  490.   | Default_specialise -> ()
  491.   | Always_specialise -> fprintf ppf "always_specialise@ "
  492.   | Never_specialise -> fprintf ppf "never_specialise@ "
  493.   end;
  494.   begin match t.local with
  495.   | Default_local -> ()
  496.   | Always_local -> fprintf ppf "always_local@ "
  497.   | Never_local -> fprintf ppf "never_local@ "
  498.   end;
  499.   if t.tmc_candidate then
  500.     fprintf ppf "tail_mod_cons@ ";
  501.   begin match t.poll with
  502.   | Default_poll -> ()
  503.   | Error_poll -> fprintf ppf "error_poll@ "
  504.   end

  506. let apply_tailcall_attribute ppf = function
  507.   | Default_tailcall -> ()
  508.   | Tailcall_expectation true ->
  509.     fprintf ppf " tailcall"
  510.   | Tailcall_expectation false ->
  511.     fprintf ppf " tailcall(false)"

  513. ‌let apply_inlined_attribute ppf = function
  514.   | Default_inline -> ()
  515.   | Always_inline -> fprintf ppf " always_inline"
  516.   | Never_inline -> fprintf ppf " never_inline"
  517.   | Hint_inline -> fprintf ppf " hint_inline"
  518.   | Unroll i -> fprintf ppf " never_inline(%i)" i

  520. ‌let apply_specialised_attribute ppf = function
  521.   | Default_specialise -> ()
  522.   | Always_specialise -> fprintf ppf " always_specialise"
  523.   | Never_specialise -> fprintf ppf " never_specialise"

  525. ‌let rec lam ppf = function
  526.   | Lvar id ->
  527.       Ident.print ppf id
  528.   | Lmutvar id ->
  529.       fprintf ppf "*%a" Ident.print id
  530.   | Lconst cst ->
  531.       struct_const ppf cst
  532.   | Lapply ap ->
  533.       let lams ppf largs =
  534.         List.iter (fun l -> fprintf ppf "@ %a" lam l) largs in
  535.       fprintf ppf "@[<2>(apply@ %a%a%a%a%a)@]" lam ap.ap_func lams ap.ap_args
  536.         apply_tailcall_attribute ap.ap_tailcall
  537.         apply_inlined_attribute ap.ap_inlined
  538.         apply_specialised_attribute ap.ap_specialised
  539.   | Lfunction{kind; params; return; body; attr} ->
  540.       let pr_params ppf params =
  541.         match kind with
  542.         | Curried ->
  543.             List.iter (fun (param, k) ->
  544.                 fprintf ppf "@ %a%a" Ident.print param value_kind k) params
  545.         | Tupled ->
  546.             fprintf ppf " (";
  547.             let first = ref true in
  548.             List.iter
  549.               (fun (param, k) ->
  550.                 if !first then first := false else fprintf ppf ",@ ";
  551.                 Ident.print ppf param;
  552.                 value_kind ppf k)
  553.               params;
  554.             fprintf ppf ")" in
  555.       fprintf ppf "@[<2>(function%a@ %a%a%a)@]" pr_params params
  556.         function_attribute attr return_kind return lam body
  557.   | Llet(_, k, id, arg, body)
  558.   | Lmutlet(k, id, arg, body) as l ->
  559.       let let_kind = begin function
  560.         | Llet(str,_,_,_,_) ->
  561.            begin match str with
  562.              Alias -> "a" | Strict -> "" | StrictOpt -> "o"
  563.            end
  564.         | Lmutlet _ -> "mut"
  565.         | _ -> assert false
  566.         end
  567.       in
  568.       let rec letbody = function
  569.         | Llet(_, k, id, arg, body)
  570.         | Lmutlet(k, id, arg, body) as l ->
  571.            fprintf ppf "@ @[<2>%a =%s%a@ %a@]"
  572.              Ident.print id (let_kind l) value_kind k lam arg;
  573.            letbody body
  574.         | expr -> expr in
  575.       fprintf ppf "@[<2>(let@ @[<hv 1>(@[<2>%a =%s%a@ %a@]"
  576.         Ident.print id (let_kind l) value_kind k lam arg;
  577.       let expr = letbody body in
  578.       fprintf ppf ")@]@ %a)@]" lam expr
  579.   | Lletrec(id_arg_list, body) ->
  580.       let bindings ppf id_arg_list =
  581.         let spc = ref false in
  582.         List.iter
  583.           (fun (id, l) ->
  584.             if !spc then fprintf ppf "@ " else spc := true;
  585.             fprintf ppf "@[<2>%a@ %a@]" Ident.print id lam l)
  586.           id_arg_list in
  587.       fprintf ppf
  588.         "@[<2>(letrec@ (@[<hv 1>%a@])@ %a)@]" bindings id_arg_list lam body
  589.   | Lprim(prim, largs, _) ->
  590.       let lams ppf largs =
  591.         List.iter (fun l -> fprintf ppf "@ %a" lam l) largs in
  592.       fprintf ppf "@[<2>(%a%a)@]" primitive prim lams largs
  593.   | Lswitch(larg, sw, _loc) ->
  594.       let switch ppf sw =
  595.         let spc = ref false in
  596.         List.iter
  597.          (fun (n, l) ->
  598.            if !spc then fprintf ppf "@ " else spc := true;
  599.            fprintf ppf "@[<hv 1>case int %i:@ %a@]" n lam l)
  600.          sw.sw_consts;
  601.         List.iter
  602.           (fun (n, l) ->
  603.             if !spc then fprintf ppf "@ " else spc := true;
  604.             fprintf ppf "@[<hv 1>case tag %i:@ %a@]" n lam l)
  605.           sw.sw_blocks ;
  606.         begin match sw.sw_failaction with
  607.         | None  -> ()
  608.         | Some l ->
  609.             if !spc then fprintf ppf "@ " else spc := true;
  610.             fprintf ppf "@[<hv 1>default:@ %a@]" lam l
  611.         end in
  612.       fprintf ppf
  613.        "@[<1>(%s %a@ @[<v 0>%a@])@]"
  614.        (match sw.sw_failaction with None -> "switch*" | _ -> "switch")
  615.        lam larg switch sw
  616.   | Lstringswitch(arg, cases, default, _) ->
  617.       let switch ppf cases =
  618.         let spc = ref false in
  619.         List.iter
  620.          (fun (s, l) ->
  621.            if !spc then fprintf ppf "@ " else spc := true;
  622.            fprintf ppf "@[<hv 1>case \"%s\":@ %a@]" (String.escaped s) lam l)
  623.           cases;
  624.         begin match default with
  625.         | Some default ->
  626.             if !spc then fprintf ppf "@ " else spc := true;
  627.             fprintf ppf "@[<hv 1>default:@ %a@]" lam default
  628.         | None -> ()
  629.         end in
  630.       fprintf ppf
  631.        "@[<1>(stringswitch %a@ @[<v 0>%a@])@]" lam arg switch cases
  632.   | Lstaticraise (i, ls)  ->
  633.       let lams ppf largs =
  634.         List.iter (fun l -> fprintf ppf "@ %a" lam l) largs in
  635.       fprintf ppf "@[<2>(exit@ %d%a)@]" i lams ls;
  636.   | Lstaticcatch(lbody, (i, vars), lhandler) ->
  637.       fprintf ppf "@[<2>(catch@ %a@;<1 -1>with (%d%a)@ %a)@]"
  638.         lam lbody i
  639.         (fun ppf vars ->
  640.            List.iter
  641.              (fun (x, k) -> fprintf ppf " %a%a" Ident.print x value_kind k)
  642.              vars
  643.         )
  644.         vars
  645.         lam lhandler
  646.   | Ltrywith(lbody, param, lhandler) ->
  647.       fprintf ppf "@[<2>(try@ %a@;<1 -1>with %a@ %a)@]"
  648.         lam lbody Ident.print param lam lhandler
  649.   | Lifthenelse(lcond, lif, lelse) ->
  650.       fprintf ppf "@[<2>(if@ %a@ %a@ %a)@]" lam lcond lam lif lam lelse
  651.   | Lsequence(l1, l2) ->
  652.       fprintf ppf "@[<2>(seq@ %a@ %a)@]" lam l1 sequence l2
  653.   | Lwhile(lcond, lbody) ->
  654.       fprintf ppf "@[<2>(while@ %a@ %a)@]" lam lcond lam lbody
  655.   | Lfor(param, lo, hi, dir, body) ->
  656.       fprintf ppf "@[<2>(for %a@ %a@ %s@ %a@ %a)@]"
  657.        Ident.print param lam lo
  658.        (match dir with Upto -> "to" | Downto -> "downto")
  659.        lam hi lam body
  660.   | Lassign(id, expr) ->
  661.       fprintf ppf "@[<2>(assign@ %a@ %a)@]" Ident.print id lam expr
  662.   | Lsend (k, met, obj, largs, _) ->
  663.       let args ppf largs =
  664.         List.iter (fun l -> fprintf ppf "@ %a" lam l) largs in
  665.       let kind =
  666.         if k = Self then "self" else if k = Cached then "cache" else "" in
  667.       fprintf ppf "@[<2>(send%s@ %a@ %a%a)@]" kind lam obj lam met args largs
  668.   | Levent(expr, ev) ->
  669. ‌      let kind =
  670.        match ev.lev_kind with
  671.        | Lev_before -> "before"
  672.        | Lev_after _  -> "after"
  673.        | Lev_function -> "funct-body"
  674.        | Lev_pseudo -> "pseudo"
  675.       in
  676.       (* -dno-locations also hides the placement of debug events;
  677.          this is good for the readability of the resulting output (usually
  678.          the end-user goal when using -dno-locations), as it strongly
  679.          reduces the nesting level of subterms. *)
  680.       if not !Clflags.locations then lam ppf expr
  681.       else begin match ev.lev_loc with
  682.       | Loc_unknown ->
  683.         fprintf ppf "@[<2>(%s <unknown location>@ %a)@]" kind lam expr
  684.       | Loc_known {scopes; loc} ->
  685.         fprintf ppf "@[<2>(%s %s %s(%i)%s:%i-%i@ %a)@]" kind
  686.                 (Debuginfo.Scoped_location.string_of_scopes scopes)
  687.                 loc.Location.loc_start.Lexing.pos_fname
  688.                 loc.Location.loc_start.Lexing.pos_lnum
  689.                 (if loc.Location.loc_ghost then "<ghost>" else "")
  690.                 loc.Location.loc_start.Lexing.pos_cnum
  691.                 loc.Location.loc_end.Lexing.pos_cnum
  692.                 lam expr
  693.       end
  694.   | Lifused(id, expr) ->
  695.       fprintf ppf "@[<2>(ifused@ %a@ %a)@]" Ident.print id lam expr

  697. ‌and sequence ppf = function
  698.   | Lsequence(l1, l2) ->
  699.       fprintf ppf "%a@ %a" sequence l1 sequence l2
  700.   | l ->
  701.       lam ppf l

  703. ‌let structured_constant = struct_const

  705. ‌let lambda = lam

  707. ‌let program ppf { code } = lambda ppf code
